# Security & Privacy Compliance

## OWASP Top 10 (Web Game Context)
- **Injection**: Sanitize all player input (chat, names, custom data) before processing or rendering. Never use `eval()` or `innerHTML` with user data.
- **Broken Auth**: Use secure session tokens, not predictable IDs. Validate sessions server-side.
- **Sensitive Data Exposure**: Never log PII, passwords, tokens, or session IDs. Never send secrets to the client.
- **XSS**: Escape all user-generated content rendered in DOM. Phaser canvas rendering is inherently safer but UI overlays are vulnerable.
- **CSRF**: Use anti-CSRF tokens on any state-changing HTTP endpoints.
- **Insecure Dependencies**: Run `npm audit` before each release. No known critical vulnerabilities in production.

## NIST 800-63 / 800-53 (Applicable Controls)
- Use HTTPS for all network communication (WebSocket over WSS, not WS)
- Implement rate limiting on server endpoints to prevent abuse
- Log security-relevant events (auth attempts, permission changes) with timestamps
- Enforce least privilege — clients can only send actions they're allowed to perform

## GDPR (EU) Requirements
- **Lawful basis**: Only collect data necessary for gameplay. Document the basis.
- **Data minimization**: Don't store what you don't need. No analytics without consent.
- **Right to erasure**: Players must be able to delete their data.
- **Consent**: Cookie/tracking consent required before any non-essential storage.
- **Privacy policy**: Must be accessible from the game UI.

## CCPA (California) Requirements
- **Right to know**: Disclose what data is collected and why.
- **Right to delete**: Honor deletion requests within 45 days.
- **Right to opt-out**: Provide opt-out for data selling (if applicable).
- **No discrimination**: Don't degrade the game experience for users who exercise rights.

## Implementation Rules
```typescript
// ❌ BAD — logging PII
logger.info("Player joined", { email: player.email, ip: req.ip });

// ✅ GOOD — log only non-PII identifiers
logger.info("Player joined", { playerId: player.id, roomId: room.id });
```

- Never store plaintext credentials
- Validate and sanitize all WebSocket messages server-side
- Use Content-Security-Policy headers in production builds
- All third-party scripts require review and documentation
